        "description": "* 3+ years of front-end technologist, engineer, or UX prototyper experience\n* Have an available online portfolio\n* Have coding samples in front end programming languages\n* 3+ years of ad or design agency experience\n* Excellent written\/verbal communication, presentation, interpersonal and analytical skills\n* Understanding and fluent usage across a broad spectrum of technologies including (but not limited to): React\/JavaScript\/NodeJS, HTML\/CSS, XML\/JSON, and Responsive\/Adaptive Design\n* Whiteboarding, which is included of the hiring process\n* Fluent in Adobe Creative Suite applications including Media Encoder, After Effects, and Photoshop\n* Understanding of WCAG AA standards and accessibility fluency\n* Experience using Figma to translate designs to websites\n* Experience using AWS in production environments\n* Understanding of performance and how to mitigate latency issues\n* Experience building work to high accessibility standards\n\n\nDesign Technology is Amazon Brand Innovation Lab\u2019s custom development and prototyping team that works with advertisers, 1p teams, and agencies. We focus on the conception, prototyping, and execution of branded custom experiences across the Amazon canvas. In agencies, such roles are often called Creative Technologists.\n  \n  \n\nAs a member of the Brand Innovation Lab\u2019s Design Technologists you will split your time between execution and strategy. You will contribute to the definition of new ad products, pre-sales prototypes, and custom campaign executions, all while working directly with Art, Copy, Interactive Experience Designers, Product Managers, Producers and Account teams.\n  \n  \n\nYou will have comprehensive understanding of the current state \u2013 and future \u2013 of web technology with a critical awareness of implications on user-centered design. You have strong communication skills and are comfortable with a range of technologies: React\/JavaScript\/NodeJS, HTML\/CSS, XML\/JSON, Adobe Creative Suite, WCAG AA\/accessibility standards, GenAI\/LLMs, and have experience with Figma and AWS.\n  \n  \n\nYou are customer-obsessed, detail-oriented, comfortable working on highly technical teams and are skilled in collaboration with non-technical creative counterparts. You are a leader in the never-ending process of improving your own and your team\u2019s standards, writing documentation, and are able to handle multiple projects in a high-velocity environment with a high-level of autonomy. You can translate business requirements into bar-raising customer experiences by thinking first from a customer\u2019s perspective and setting relentlessly high standards to achieve them.\n  \n  \n\nYou are equally passionate about design and development. You have strong front-end proficiency, are a creative problem solver at the core and have a keen eye for world class functional design. You will bring disruptive ideas for how to concept, create, and deliver branded shopping experiences for millions of customers worldwide and work across desktop, mobile, Fire tablet, Fire TV, Alexa, Twitch, Amazon Live and other Amazon properties.\n  \n  \n\nKey job responsibilities\n  \n  \n\n**Responsibilities include:**  \n\n* Own the end-to-end development process and deliverables from a design and technical perspective\n* Provide design and technical leadership; work closely with business teams in development of campaign strategy, use cases, and technical requirements\n* Concept first-to-market innovations that utilize Amazon\u2019s canvas alongside creative counterparts\n* Present work to peers, product teams and Senior leadership\n* Provide leadership, mentor, and coach to your immediate and extended team\n* Partner with program and product managers to appropriately identify and assess features for future product offerings\n\n\n**Here are some things that we\u2019re looking for:**  \n\n* Proven web development experience across multiple devices, web-views and browsers\n* Proven ability to simplify complex problems into intuitive and elegant experiences\n* Ability to deliver functional prototypes on various devices\n* Ability to communicate complex concepts clearly and persuasively across different audiences and varying levels of the organization\n* Ability to participate in the full lifecycle of design and development \u2013 including ideation, prototyping, development, backwards compatibility, fail-overs, validation, and user-testing\n\n\nPlease include your online portfolio and process examples in your application.\n  \n  \n\nAbout the team\n  \nBrand Innovation Lab is dedicated to crafting innovative advertising campaigns and products that enable brands to distinguish themselves on Amazon. We aim to captivate our mutual customers by facilitating new discoveries, rewarding engagement, and assisting in informed purchasing decisions.\n  \n  \n\nRecognizing the continuously evolving expectations of both customers and brands, Design Technologists explore new innovation avenues for brands to come to life on Amazon.\n  \n  \n\n* Familiar with creative ideation and brainstorm sessions with internal and external partners\n* Familiarity with Android and\/or iOS development\n* Familiarity with GenAI\/LLMs, Augmented Reality, Virtual Reality, Alexa, Voice Design\n* BS\/MS in computer science, technology, design, or equivalent professional experience\n\n\nAmazon is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace. Amazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, protected veteran status, disability, age, or other legally protected status. For individuals with disabilities who would like to request an accommodation, please visit https:\/\/www.amazon.jobs\/en\/disability\/us.\n  \n  \n\nOur compensation reflects the cost of labor across several US geographic markets. The base pay for this position ranges from $118,600\/year in our lowest geographic market up to $205,000\/year in our highest geographic market. Pay is based on a number of factors including market location and may vary depending on job-related knowledge, skills, and experience. Amazon is a total compensation company. Dependent on the position offered, equity, sign-on payments, and other forms of compensation may be provided as part of a total compensation package, in addition to a full range of medical, financial, and\/or other benefits. For more information, please visit https:\/\/www.aboutamazon.com\/workplace\/employee-benefits. This position will remain posted until filled. Applicants should apply via our internal or external career site.",
