        "description": "**Job Title:** **Product Manager \u2013 Data Platforms & Business Intelligence**\n**Area:** **IT Data Management**\n**Reports to:** **Director, Data Management**\n**Classification:** **Exempt**\n**Location:** **Evanston, IL**\n*This position is designated as* ***Hybrid - Fully Flexible*** *and expected to work from our World Headquarters office once per month to several times a week. The specific days in the office are determined by managers based on business requirements. Rotary is under the jurisdiction of Illinois employment laws; we require all employees to live within reasonable daily commuting distance to Evanston.*\n\n**Organization Overview**\nRotary is a membership organization that unites people from all continents and cultures who take action to deliver real, long-term solutions to pressing issues facing our communities and the world. Each year, Rotary members expand their networks, build lasting relationships, and invest more than $300 million and 16 million volunteer hours to improve lives and create positive change in the world. In exchange for hard work and dedication in support of Rotary\u2019s clubs, members and other participants, and their humanitarian service projects, our employees receive competitive salaries, flexible schedules, comprehensive benefits, and job enrichment. To learn more, visit http:\/\/www.rotary.org.\n**Rotary\u2019s Commitment to Diversity**\nAs a global network that strives to build a world where people unite and take action to create lasting change, Rotary values diversity and celebrates the contributions of people of all backgrounds, regardless of their age, ethnicity, race, color, abilities, religion, socioeconomic status, culture, sex, sexual orientation, and gender identity.\n**Overview**\nThe Product Manager - Data Platforms and Business Intelligence reports to the Director - Data Management and is primarily responsible for Rotary\u2019s business intelligence functionality and data platforms. This role manages the data platforms, architecture, technologies, and methodologies used in Rotary\u2019s business intelligence related services and works closely with the Product Manager - Data Governance & CRM to assist with defining and maintaining the rules and process to maintain Rotary\u2019s data.\n**You Will have**\n* Bachelor\u2019s degree in computer science, data business, information technology, or related field. MBA or master\u2019s degree is a plus.\n* At least 5 years of management experience with data warehouses or data lakes, business intelligence related services, and data platforms, architectures, technologies, and methodologies.\n* Experience managing large-scale and complex data programs and projects that involve multiple teams and stakeholders.\n* Proven experience as a strong cross-group collaborator and team player, dealing with complex problems, resolving conflicts, and experience influencing cross-functionality, and with executive-level audiences.\n* Ability to quickly adapt to shifting priorities, demands and timelines through both analytical and problem-solving capabilities.\n* Ability to manage and motivate a team to achieve results, focusing on the positive, regardless of the obstacles.\n* Ability to work independently and well under pressure and perform multiple concurrent and diversified tasks effectively.\n* Excellent interpersonal, written, and oral communication skills.\n* Excellent time management, organizational, customer service, and problem-solving skills.\n* Strong team player, self-motivated and detail oriented.\n* Proficient in Microsoft Office (Outlook, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint).\n\n**You Are Good At**\n* Communication (written and verbal)\n* Decision Making\n* Interpersonal Effectiveness\n* Productivity\n* Self-Management\n* Service Orientation\n* Professional Development\n\n**You Will Be Responsible For**\n* Managing a product owner, data engineer, and team of offshore development and quality assurance engineers.\n* Owning the process for defining and promoting Rotary\u2019s data platform and business information strategy and architecture.\n* Coordinating and prioritizing the delivery of requested improvements and functionality to Rotary\u2019s enterprise data and business information platforms.\n* Defining and documenting the current and future state of data platform and business information architecture, roadmaps, and action plans.\n* Working closely with the Product Manager - Data Governance & CRM, contribute to the development of enterprise data policies, including such things as data stewardship, data governance, audit requirements and service level agreements (SLAs) to support the quality and use of information.\n* Establishing and promoting enterprise business information management principles, models, best practices, and standards and works to ensure their practical adoption.\n* Establishing and communicating key metrics related to the health of Rotary\u2019s business information environment and quality of data stored.\n* Working closely with data analysts across the organization to enable self-service analytics and reporting.\n* Monitoring and optimization of the data platform cloud costs.\n* Occasional weekend and\/or evening work\n* Other duties as assigned.\n\n**Leadership Attributes**\n* **Collaboration:** Builds partnerships and works jointly with others to meet shared objectives.\n* **Productivity:** Able to generate results that moves Rotary toward achieving its goals.\n* **Accountability:** Have a clear sense of ownership and take personal responsibility for actions.\n* **Adaptability:** **Respond to changes willingly and recognize when to adjust based on the situation.**\n\n**Why Work for Rotary?**\n* Generous medical, dental, and vision benefits package\n* Progressive 401k matching contributions\n* Above market and generous paid time off package\n* Tuition reimbursement\n* Professional development opportunities\n* On-site cafeteria and coffee bar with special pricing for Rotary employees\n* Flextime-several different work schedules to choose from\n* Close to CTA, Metra, a variety of stores, and many food options\n\n**Please note:**\n* Rotary does not provide VISA sponsorship or relocation assistance",
