        "description": "Description:HOH Water Technology is a leading, growing, third generation water treatment company celebrating 56 years of business, seeking an experienced and dynamic Product Manager focused on Boiler and Cooling Towers to join our team. As a Product Manager for Boiler and Cooling, you will play a pivotal role of driving success of our heating and cooling industrial water system product line. Your objectives will include, bridging the gap between business goals, client needs, and technical execution for products & services within this scope, alongside the Technical Director. Your responsibilities will span client facing technical support and troubleshooting, continuous improvement program management and product line management. This is a full-time position, and we are seeking a candidate located in the vicinity of clients in the Midwest, ideally in the Chicagoland area. This position offers flexibility with remote, hybrid or in-office work arrangement at our Palatine, IL office. If you thrive in a collaborative environment and have a passion for delivering innovative solutions, we want to hear from you! \n\n  \n\n\n**What we offer:**\n\n* Salary range $80,000-$120,000 based on experience\n* **Full Benefits**: Medical and Dental Insurance with a generous employer contribution, Company Contributed HSA Contribution of $1200 family\/$800 Individual annually, 401K with company matching, 15 PTO Days\/14 Paid Holidays, paid birthday off, Company provided Life Insurance and Long-term disability, Short-Term Disability, Hospital, Critical Illness, FSA available, Health Club Reimbursement & Company Profit-Sharing Bonus (opportunity to achieve 3-4 week of salary in bonus pay)\n* Company provided vehicle, cell phone and laptop\n* **Flexibility** while working from home office and traveling to customers\n* **Strong Culture**- Caring Leadership, High Engagement (4.62\/5 Gallup Q12 score), Team and Company Events\n* **Career Growth**- Hands-On training, Employee Development, Manager Investment, Continuing Education Reimbursement\n\n**Main responsibilities of the position include:**\n\n* Act as the primary technical resource for troubleshooting boiler and cooling tower industrial water systems.\n* Provide regular training to Sales and Service teams on the assigned product line, ensuring they are well-versed in technical documentation and tools.\n* Collaborate with sales and service teams to effectively communicate technical aspects to end users and recommend tailored technical solutions to meet client needs.\n* Conduct program audits, to drive continuous improvement. Working closely with Business Development Managers and Water Quality Engineers to cross-sell and implement projects identified through the program audits.\n* Establish feedback loops to enhance the product based on user insights and market changes.\n* Maintain up-to-date supporting documents, including Product Data Sheets, Case Studies, Product Application Guides, and ERP & CRM product files.\n* Oversee the entire product lifecycle, from ideation to launch and beyond.\n* Present product updates, performance metrics, and strategic outcomes to executive leadership and stakeholders.\n* Monitor key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure product success.\n\nRequirements:* At least 5 years of experience with boiler and cooling tower water treatment industrial sector. Proven experience in product management, technical support, audits or related roles.\n* Candidate must have excellent communication and presentation abilities. Organizational skills, detail oriented, and result driven mindset with a passion for driving product excellence. A high level of dedication to be a team player.\n* Strong analytical skills and the ability to translate technical information into actionable insights.\n* Bachelor\u2019s or Master\u2019s degree in Engineering, Business, or a related field, preferred but if the candidate has no degree, then the candidate must have obtained knowledge in the field through a combination of work experience and intellectual instruction.\n* Must pass a Human Performance Evaluation (HPE), Motor Vehicle Report (MVR), Drug Screening and background check.\n* Must be able to sit for extended periods of time driving to customer sites\n* Must be in good physical condition: frequent walking to customer sites, may perform physical work such as climbing stairs or ladders, sometimes moving drums of chemical\n* Must be willing to work in environments with hot and cold temperatures, exposure to chemicals, noise, wearing proper PPE on face, ears, hands\n* Must be able to communicate in English and ability to read proficiently in English\n* Must be legally authorized to work in the U.S.\n\n Join our team and contribute to shaping the future of industrial water systems.",
