        "description": "**Job Description:**\n\nWe are currently looking for a meticulous and detail-oriented Quality Analyst to join our dynamic team. As a Quality Analyst, you will play a pivotal role in ensuring the highest standards of quality and compliance within our organization. Your dedication to maintaining regulatory standards and optimizing processes will contribute significantly to our overall success.\n\n**Overview:**\n\nAs a Quality Analyst, you will be responsible for monitoring and evaluating processes to uphold quality standards and compliance with regulatory requirements. Your keen eye for detail and analytical skills will be essential in identifying areas for improvement and implementing effective quality control measures.\n\n**Duties:**\n\n- Conduct thorough quality assessments to ensure adherence to Medicare, ICD-9, ICD-10, FDA regulations, JCAHO, coding, HIPAA, and other relevant standards.  \n- Develop and implement quality assurance procedures to enhance compliance management and operational efficiency.  \n- Analyze data and performance metrics to identify trends, patterns, and areas of non-compliance.  \n- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to address quality issues and implement corrective actions.  \n- Prepare detailed reports on quality findings and recommendations for management review.  \n- Participate in internal and external audits to validate compliance with regulatory requirements.  \n- Stay updated on industry best practices and regulatory changes to ensure continuous improvement in quality processes.\n\n**Qualifications:**\n\n- Bachelor's degree in a related field or equivalent work experience.  \n- Proven experience in quality assurance, preferably in a healthcare or regulated industry.  \n- In-depth knowledge of Medicare, ICD-9, ICD-10, FDA regulations, JCAHO, coding, HIPAA, and compliance management.  \n- Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret complex data sets.  \n- Excellent communication skills with the ability to collaborate effectively across teams.  \n- Detail-oriented mindset with a focus on accuracy and precision.  \n- Certification in quality management or related field is a plus.\n\nJoin our team as a Quality Analyst and contribute to our commitment to delivering high-quality services while ensuring compliance with industry regulations. Your expertise will be instrumental in driving continuous improvement and maintaining excellence in our operations.\n\nJob Type: Contract\n\nPay: $45.00 - $50.00 per hour\n\nExpected hours: 40 per week\n\nSchedule:\n\n* 8 hour shift\n* Monday to Friday\n\nEducation:\n\n* Bachelor's (Required)\n\nExperience:\n\n* Quality Improvement Analyst: 2 years (Required)\n\nLanguage:\n\n* Bilingual (Preferred)\n\nAbility to Commute:\n\n* Costa Mesa, CA 92626 (Required)\n\nWork Location: In person",
