        "description": "**Junior Design Engineer** \n\n**Location: Skokie,IL**\n\nWe are seeking a passionate and driven Junior Design Engineer to join our innovative team. If you are a recent graduate or have 1-2 years of hands-on design experience, this is an excellent opportunity to grow your career in a dynamic environment where you can learn all aspects of engineering.\n\n**Key Responsibilities:**\n\n* Spend 60% of your time designing in 3D CAD, specifically in SolidWorks, although experience with other 3D CAD software (AutoCAD, Creo, Inventor) is acceptable.\n* Assist in design changes, creating drawings, and performing calculations.\n* Spend 40% of your time on the shop floor, providing plant support on quality issues, manufacturing questions, and clarifications on drawings.\n* Be hands-on in a machining environment, addressing practical engineering challenges.\n* Work primarily with carbon steel, with occasional projects involving aluminum.\n\n**Qualifications:**\n\n* Bachelor\u2019s Degree in Mechanical Engineering is required.\n* 1-2 years of hands-on design experience preferred; new graduates with strong internships will be considered.\n* Proficiency in 3D CAD software, ideally SolidWorks, but experience with AutoCAD, Creo, or Inventor is also acceptable.\n* A proactive, go-getter attitude with a strong desire to learn and grow.\n* Ability to wear multiple hats, assisting with quality issues, manufacturing questions, and bringing in new designs.\n* Excellent teamwork skills and a willingness to support various aspects of the engineering process.\n\n**Preferred Skills:**\n\n* Experience in a machining environment or designing machined components, mechanical components like valves, filters, bearings, or motor components.\n* Basic understanding of GD&T (Geometric Dimensioning and Tolerancing) is a significant plus.\n* Avoiding experience primarily in injection molding or plastic-related fields, as this differs significantly from our work.\n\n**Why Join Us?**\n\n* Opportunity to gain comprehensive engineering experience, from design to hands-on shop floor support.\n* Work in a collaborative and supportive environment that values continuous learning and growth.\n* Be part of a company that machines everything in-house, providing unique hands-on experience with the entire production process.\n\nIf you are a motivated and versatile individual with a strong mechanical engineering background and a desire to dive into all facets of engineering, we encourage you to apply. Join us and become a key player in our engineering team!",
